And Jacob was the son of Joseph, a man of Mary the wife of him who was called Jesus, whom they called the Christ.
And from all the generations of Abraham to David were fourteen generations, and from David to the Babylonian captivity fourteen generations, and from the Babylonian captivity to the Messiah fourteen generations. The birth of Jesus the Christ.
And the birth of Jesus the Messiah was as follows: When Mary his mother was betrothed to Joseph, before they had come together, she was found with child by the Holy Spirit.
He covered his wife's feet, for he was a righteous man, and he did not wish to reveal her to anyone, desiring to keep it secret.
But reflecting on these matters, if the angel of the Lord had appeared to him in a dream and said, “O Joseph, son of David, do not fear to take Mary your wife, for he who is conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.”
“And you will be born and call his name Jesus, for he will save your people from their sins.”
And all this was so that what was said by God through the prophet might be fulfilled:
Behold, the Virgin conceives and gives birth to a son, and they call his name Emmanuel, which means: God is with us.
And when Joseph awoke from his sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded him, and took his wife.
She didn't know him until she gave birth to her first son. And he named him Jesus.
Visit of the Magi
And when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea, in the days of Herod the king, behold, magi from the east came to Jerusalem
They say, “Where is the newborn King of the Jews? For we have seen his star in the East and have come to do homage to him.”
And when Herod the king heard it, he was troubled, together with all Jerusalem.
He gathered all the heads of the priests and the scribes of the people, and asked them: “Where is the Messiah to be born?”
They said to him, “In Bethlehem of Judea, for because he has come to pass that it is written, ‘A child is born to us, in the Lord.’”
And you, Bethlehem, the land of Judah, are not small among the chiefs of Judah, for from you there shall come forth the one who will rule and lead the people of Israel.
Then Herod summoned the Magi secretly, and when the time of the wise man had come, which was told him by an astrologer.
Then he sent them to Bethlehem and said, “Go and search diligently for the child. And when you have found him, come back to me so that I may also go and pay my respects to him.”
And when they heard from the king, they departed. And if the star that they had seen in the east, went before them until it came and stood over, where the boy was.
And when they saw the star, they rejoiced with a very great rejoicing.
And they came to the House, and they saw the boy with Mary his mother. They rejoiced and prostrated themselves before him. Then they opened their treasures and presented to him gifts: gold and frankincense and myrrh.
Then, when it was revealed to them in a dream that they should not return to Herod, they took another way to their retreat. Escape to Egypt.
After they had departed, if the angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream saying: “Arise and take the boy and his mother and flee to Egypt, and be there until I tell you. For Herod is set on seeking the boy in order to destroy him.”
He took the boy and his mother at night and went to Egypt.
And there was until Herod’s death. In order that the saying of God might be fulfilled which the prophet had spoken: “Out of Egypt have I called my son.”
Then, when Herod saw that the Magi had mocked him, he was very angry. So he sent and killed all the boys in Bethlehem and in all its surroundings, from two years old and down, according to the time that the Magi had ascertained from the astrologers.
Then it was done as was said of Jeremiah the prophet, who declared:
A sound was heard in Ramah, a great cry of Noah and wailing. Rachel wept for her children and did not want to be comforted, for they were not there. Return to Nazareth.
And when Herod died, then an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt
He said, “Go and take the boy and his mother and go to the land of Israel, for those who were seeking the boy are dead.”
He took the boy and his mother and came to the land of Israel.
But when he heard that Archelaus possessed the kingdom instead of his father Herod, he feared to go there. And when an angel told him in a dream, he withdrew to the regions of Galilee.
And he came and settled in a city called Naserah, so that what was said about the prophets might be fulfilled: “Behold, Nersah will be called.”
John the Baptist is preparing the way.
And in those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Judea
He said, “Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near.”
And this is what was said about him by Isaiah the prophet, who declared: “A voice cries out in the wilderness, ‘Prepare the way of the Lord.’ Make all his valleys clear and smooth.”
And John wore a garment woven from the hair of camels, and about his loins was a sash of leather. His food was honey and green figs.
And then Jerusalem and all the Jews of the province, and all the surrounding countries came unto him.
And rely on Him in Jordan, acknowledging their sins.
And when many of the Pharisees and Sadducees came to the baptism, he said to them, “You snakes! From the wrath that is to come?”
Cultivate fruits befitting repentance.
And do not think in your hearts: “For us alone have we Abraham.” I say to you that God is able to make descendants of these stones for Abraham.
And now, I have placed the axe at the root of the tree, so every tree that does not bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.
I offer you water for repentance, but that which comes after me is stronger than I, one whom I am not worthy to carry his sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.
which he will wipe with his hand, and purify with his threshing-floors, and will gather his wheat into the granary, and as for the chaff he will burn it with a fire that will not be extinguished.” The baptism of Jesus Christ
Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan, to be baptized by John.
But John forbade him, saying, “I need you to depend on me, and you come to me!”
And Jesus answered him and said, “Be it done now, for this day is needful for us, that we may finish this offering.” Then he allowed him to do it.
And when Jesus had been baptized, he ascended from the water, and immediately the heavens were opened, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove, and it came to pass that a certain voice said to him, “You are my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.”
And a voice from the heavens said: “This is my beloved Son, in whom I delight.”
Jesus faces the ordeal
Then Jesus ascended into the wilderness by the Spirit to be tempted by Satan.
After he fasted for forty days and forty nights, he finally became hungry.
He then presented the sorcerer and said to him: “If you are the son of God, say that these stones shall become bread.”
And he replied, “It is written: ‘Not by bread alone does man live, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.’”
Then Satan took him to the Holy City and set him on the wing of the temple.
He said to him, “If you are the son of God, then throw yourself down to the depths, for it is written that He commands His angels to protect you, and in their hands they will carry you so that you may not strike your foot against a stone.”
Jesus said to him, “It is also written, ‘You shall not make mockery of God.’”
Then Satan also took him to a very high mountain, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their glory.
He said to him, “I will give it all to you if you fall down and bow to me.”
And Jesus said to him, “You shall go out with the devil! For it is written, ‘Worship the Lord your God, and serve him only.’”
Then Satan left him, and if angels came, they served him. The beginning of his service was in Galilee.
And when Jesus heard that John had been delivered up, He departed into Galilee.
And he left Nazareth and came and settled in Capernaum, which is by the sea, at the borders of Zebulun and Naphtali.
In order to fulfill what was said by the prophet Isaiah:
The land of Zebulun, and the land of Naphtali, beside the sea, beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles.
The people who were sitting in darkness have seen a great light, and those who were sitting in the pit have seen a bright light.
From that time on, Jesus began to preach and say, “Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.” The call of the first disciples
And as Jesus was passing by the Sea of Galilee, he saw two men: Simon, who was called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the sea, they were fishermen.
He said to them: “Come with me, and I will make you catch men.”
At that time, they left the window and followed him.
Then he passed by them and saw two other brothers: Yaqub ibn Zibdi and his brother Yuhanna, in the boat with their father Zibdi mending their nets, so he called them.
As they sailed away, they left the ship and their father, and followed after. Jesus was teaching and healing the sick.
And Jesus was going through all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching good news, and healing every sick one.
His fame spread throughout all of Syria. So they brought to him all the sick, afflicted with various diseases and pains, the insane, the chained, and the epileptic, and he healed them.
